-- Dimon Says ‘The Buck Stops With Me’ on JPMorgan Trading Loss
-- B y   D a w n   K o p e c k i
-- 2012-06-13T16:00:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/dimon-says-the-buck-stops-with-me-on-jpmorgan-trading-loss.html
Jamie Dimon , the chairman and chief
executive officer of JPMorgan Chase & Co., said he deserves to
be blamed for a $2 billion trading loss at the bank’s chief
investment office.  “I’m absolutely responsible,” Dimon told the Senate
Banking Committee today. “The buck stops with me.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
